content: why not try monese for yourself and bag  once you make your first purchase  download the app and sign up using code stuar ive only recently signed up, as i wasnt happy with monzos recent update to their app and have to say thus far monese ticks the boxes to help me budget! i'm using the simple plan which is has no monthly fee.i did have a few issues when creating my account as their servers seemed to have an issue  but a few details, a photo of my driving licence and a quick selfi-video - my account was created and verified within  minutes. you have to then order your debit card, which im surprised isnt automatic  but its free and was delivered in only two days! not your traditional debit card as the number is on the back which i like.+ monthly spending overview graph is excellent.+ ,/mth foreign spending.+ lock/unlock debit card.+ link paypal account to the app.what could be improved- debit card should be automatically ordered once account verified.- more debit card controls  to control certain transaction types.this is a great account to keep on top of your spending and keep on budget

reply: Hello, James,We are very sorry to hear you feel this way. Please know that Monese is a registered agent by PrePay Technologies Limited which is an electronic money institution authorised by the Financial Conduct Authority under the Electronic Money Regulations 2011 (900010) for the issuing of electronic money and payment instruments. We have built our systems using the latest cloud technologies that help us safeguard your funds and data.We are required to keep our customers‚Äô deposits in segregated and safeguarded accounts in strong European banks. Unlike regular banks, we do not re-invest customer funds and have to keep all customer money separate from our own company finances. This guarantees that even in the unlikely event that Monese is no longer in business, all of our customers would receive 100% of their balance back.If you need any further clarification, feel free to let us know.All the best,The Monese Team

title: Great value for money and functionality
content: that is quite troubling, this is a bank and it has my money, support shouldn't be tiered or slow. i live and work in the uk but will be going abroad for a year or two and in that time will be working remotely for my uk employer, which means i'll be left with no uk address (as i rent) and thus no uk bank account as my (now previous) bank requires a uk address. i tried to switch to their international account, but that requires an income of k a year and an address abroad. except those in the eu, those don't qualify for international account because logic and that is where i'm going. so i was forced to look for alternatives and settled for monese because it has very low fees when spending or transferring money abroad, both g and euro account, apple/google pay, support for direct debits and standing orders, and an amazing mobile app that lets you control your account, open new ones, lock your card, etc. i'm staying on the free tier at the moment but when i go abroad and need to convert my g salary into the local currency the savings from the amazing monese exchange rate are much bigger than the cost of the monthly fee to get era benefits like cheaper exchange. checkout the current exchange rate on the monese website and what local exchanges and your bank offer - even if you are just going on a week or two holiday abroad, chances are it will be cheaper to upgrade for a month to one of the monese paid tiers (if you need the higher fee-free spending limits) and exchange/spend through them than use your bank's or local currency exchange office

name: Paulo Dias
title: Account closure and funds not returned
content: as i didnt have an uk bank account at that time i decided to open a monese bank account (end of april) so my new company could transfer their relocation support allowance to me.the process to open the bank account was quick.i got my relocation allowance transfered into monese account and also requested a debit card. i finally moved in to the uk and started to use the monese account and cards to make payments, set up first direct debits and the standing order to pay my property letting.also i have topped up the monese account by transfering money from my portuguese bank account when was necessary ( i am from portugal). i got my first uk salary transfered to this monese account and on the ne day (.) i had the standing order to pay my letting and a direct debit as well.later on that day when i was taking a look at my emails i found an email from monese as copied below:we just need to let you know that weve completed all the checks that were required to perform in order to keep your account open.unfortunately, because we couldnt gather enough information, your account will now be closed.wed like to give you some idea as to why were unable to continue servicing your account at this time.at monese, we need to make sure that the use of your monese account is compliant with certain legal requirements as issued by our regulator, the uk financial conduct authority (fca).at this time, we havent been able to verify that your account activity falls in line with these fca rules.please note that were now unable to provide you with financial statements and were unable to reopen your account.in addition, any direct debits, payrolls or subscriptions linked to your account will be discontinued due to closure of your account. if funds have recently been transferred to your account but have not yet arrived, they will be returned to the sender.you currently have xxxx.xx in account no.unfortunately, the source account from which these funds were paid is unable to receive returned transfers. in order to return the funds, we require you to provide us with the details of another account of which you are the account holdersince then i called to monese support line where they told me they cannot assist with the issue as they deal only with superficial issues (?).as it was requested on their email and then confirmed by online support advisors i have replied to the email requesting (again) more information as why account was closed without any warning and i have provided them with alternative account details so they can return my funds back to me, i asked for an estimation date to when my funds would be transfered and available for me. and the result is that i still have no answer!!!!luckily i had another account with funds available so i can have cash to make my normal life on a daily basis but i had to transfer money from my savings, transfer money from portugal to uk to pay my letting agreement, direct debit that was supposed to be paid and was not!! so far i do not have any reply to my emails and phone calls. what if this happens to someone who does not have any other funds available and have to pay bills, buy food, is currently travelling, etc.??i have read now in some reviews that this situation happened several times and people are complaining they still havent got their money back after  months
reply: Hello, Paulo,We are very sorry to hear about your negative experience. Please be advised that we only close accounts if your account usage is not in accordance with our Terms and Conditions sections 14&15. We are glad to see the remaining funds have been transferred but we sincerely apologise for any and all inconvenience this situation must have caused you.Thank you for your understanding.All the best,The Monese Team

title: Quick to take your money incredibly slow to help their customers.
content: tried to make a payment at the post office and my card declined when i had more than enough funds in the account. i am leaving for vacation in two days and needed to exchange some money ay the post office with no luck. great bank if you require a quick bank account in uk but when you actually need help they are useless
reply: Hi there,We're sad to hear about your negative experience. This is not by any means reflective of our standards of service and customer satisfaction. Upon checking your account we found out that debit card transaction was indeed declined twice at currency conversion shop which has been blocked by our card issuer for security reasons, due to high-risk appetite. Do you know Monese cards can be used anywhere in the world where Mastercard is accepted, and offer exceptionally good FX rates? probably a good idea to use your card on vacation instead of carrying a cash and paying a horrendous amount of fee during conversion.Happy to say our support team proactively called you after reading a review and explained everything in detail, gave possible alternate solutions. We hope that has helped to clear any confusion. Please do contact us if you need any further help.PS: We must also clarify that our phone line system does not let any caller wait for 30 minutes(as you mentioned) under any circumstances. Instead, every caller is promoted to receive a callback upon requesting with IVR by pressing a number 2. Best Regards,The Monese Team

reply: Hi there.We are sad to hear that things didn't go down as you expected. As per our record, you were taken care with utmost care by our very experienced support agent throughout your journey with Monese. During that, we made every possible effort to ensure we go extra mile facilitating you. It saddens us deeply that you still had to leave such negative review. Here is the break down of events which we believe is important for our readers to understand the complete situation.-Card delay was caused because of the incomplete/incorrect address entered in the App by the customer before ordering the card.-Our support staff proactively contacted and sent you 2nd debit card to Romania free of charge, which you decided not to wait until the expected delivery date and complained. -We sent a 3rd debit card using 'next day express delivery' free of charge again (You were charged for the only first card which we happily reimbursed as a goodwill gesture)-International payment was delayed because sender sent the payment via wrong payment method which isn't in our control, our support team informed you about the possible reasons of the delay and instructed how to deal with such situations (Instructions how to receive payments are clearly mentioned in the App) Lastly, if customer report issues on a public platform with negative reviews with no details, instead of contacting company support team first in that case, business have the right to approach the customer proactively and ask for more details so they can try to resolve the issue. This isn't a threat or manipulating our customer for good reviews as we do not indulge in such practices.For any further details or feedback, we kindly ask you to contact the support team directly we will be very happy to have your opinion.Best Regards,

name: Dylan Mcallister
title: AVOID! Don't Listen to the positive reviews, this is why you should AVOID!
content: if you ever run into a problem with monese, then you are never ever ever going to get your money back from them, no matter whether this is p or , you don't have a chance. however i was told that this issue would be investigated and would take up to  days, it's now the nd day, and despite me chasing almost daily, i've been called a liar and told that the cash machine dispensed the correct amount, it did not. - monese claims that it offers direct debits, whilst it does it is not able to accommodate them all (as advised by someone from monese support). i have been trying for weeks to set up a direct debit, which fails each time, meanwhile, that's putting my account into a default. - monese does not consistently notify you of money going out of in your account, my account is now a negative balance (negative balances are also possible), which no elanation as to why, and no notification, are monese just helping themselves to my money now? - monese does not offer basic banking protection, it claims to work with the fscs, i highly doubt it, i would never trust large sums of money to be put into a monese owned account. - things like standing orders are not offered, or correct direct debits, these are basic banking features. - if you ever need a refund from a pre-authorisation, you need to jump through hoops and need authorisation codes, and confirmation that the money will not be taken from your account, they don't automatically release funds into your account after a few days of them being pending, i've had payment stay pending for weeks and weeks without them being returned to my account (as they should). a month for all of the above, save some money and open a basic fee-free bank or post office account to save you the trouble. this review is as a result of genuine usage of my monese account, i'm currently in the process of compiling everything so it can be brought up with the financial ombudsman services. if you have any questions, queries or concerns, please direct yourself to the open complaint on my account

title: Beginners guide to Monese
content: if, like me, you have managed to screw your finances so dramatically that nobody wants to give you even the simplest of "proper" bank accounts, this is very likely the most useful app you will ever find for your smartphone. opening an account is a little intense to be frank, and, in the uk at least, you do require photo id and proof of address despite the claims made in the monese promotional material. another key detail, most of these banks charge for cash machine withdrawals. monese gives you five such transactions free of charge each month before adding a p fee for any subsequent withdrawals. a nice touch though, if you don't have enough money to cover the fee you will still be given the cash without charge - this might be a bug however it's been really useful for me up to now. if you could help both yourself and me by using my code hxqsehb you will be gifted  completely free when you finish setting up your new account

name: Anthony
title: Limited Service
content: my current bank is / which given the lock out meant because i wasnt able to call in office hours i was locked out and unable to register my card for nearly a week due to weekend etc. i understand the need for security, and value that but there must be an easier way plus all i need to login is an email link (when account not locked) not very secure at all. we managed to unlock the account quickly. my current bank has always been quick and even offers an automated service should the line be busy not great but least its there if you want it. there is a monthly cost after trial which again is something to consider given the limited service and support. i cant recommend over my current high street bank or other app only banks. i can get more for less so unless you send a lot of money aboard its reallly not worth the service you get and i certainly would switch to it as my main account.my story might not be a common one least i hope not, but does highlight the limits of the service
reply: Hi Anthony,Thanks a million for your review.  We always welcome feedback about how to make ours service better.  We can definitely make the lock-out process easier to resolve and hope to have a new process launched for this very shortly (this isn't an overnight process due to the need for ensuring security at all times).Our support can be busy at certain times of the week (Monday morning and Friday's in particular), but generally you should have to wait much less than 5 minutes - although we appreciate that is not the impression we gave with your wait on this occasion.  Our phone support is currently office hours, but we run in-app chat support until 22:00 every day should you need any help.  We are one of the few new banking services to offer comprehensive phone support and are working hard to improve this all the time.There is also a lot of work done in the background to ensure security with your mobile device, so although we make the process feel easy with email registration, there is a lot more we are doing that goes unseen to ensure your security.We do understand that for many people, you can get an account from a traditional high street bank under a 'free whilst in credit model', but the fees in that case are often hidden (such as charges for a refused Direct Debit where there is no charge from us) and turn up as a surprise.  We prefer that charges are up front and something that can be relied upon.As always, we highly appreciate your feedback about how we make our service better and would love to chat if you have any other feedback.  Just drop us a line to support@monese.com and we will call you back.The Monese Team

Apple/Android pay are both coming (in the works now) - Android Pay is likely to be slightly faster to market than Apple Pay (more down to respective processes at the other end than our side).  On Faster Payments, all out-going payments are made at a maximum of 30 minutes.  Incoming has been slightly slower until now, but will be moving to every 30mins early next week (after final testing this week).  We are also working on real-time faster payments and expect to have these implemented around the end of the year.   You can of course make instant faster payments to any other Monese user anywhere in Europe (whether they have a UK account or a European IBAN account) - although we realise that not everybody is a Monese user yet üòâ.  Let us know if you have any issues paying into our new European IBANs (they are live on the Step2 SEPA platform) as we are following up on every instance where there are issues - we realise there will be a few, even thought we have done extensive testing across Europe.  Localised IBANs are also in the works but will take another few months to be finalised.  Keep in touch and thanks again.The Monese Team

reply: Hi Mark,Let me start by saying we are sorry for the unauthorised transactions. Thank you for calling in and we are happy we resolved the issue. It was a very peculiar incident for anything to slip through our extremely stringent anti-fraud checks and especially due to the very small value of the transactions which is impossible to withdraw from an ATM. We are diligently looking into this and we will keep you updated, Mark.Let us also say thank you so much for the in depth review! We are so happy that you are enjoying everything about Monese, bar the above incident, and the addition of Direct Debits now means that you are using us as your main account! We are so glad to have you on the Monese team and hope that we keeping shipping features that you love!All the best from us at Monese!

name: Rachel clarke
title: Reassured after being given accurate information.
content: re-rating as a  as very happy with the account management and the add on euro card account. happy to confirm account is fine with minimal stress rating as a  now as would still prefer a visa card!*************** old review below ***************** not very happy withe account changes. direct debits are not need and would prefer to have a visa card having mastercard with a different account. also noticed you are starting to credit check people "use an id verification agency or credit reference agency both prior to and following issue of your monese account for this purpose and who will add details to your record of our request for a search."how is this going to work for people who live outside the uk? and what about people who joined you because they had a bad credit history?
reply: Hi Rachel,We are sorry that you are not a fan of the account upgrade! Direct Debits enable us to be on feature parity with traditional banks and are a necessity for most of our customers so that they can pay bills or rent as Monese is their main and only account. In regards to switching to Mastercard, we felt that we could offer more with them and so switched but we appreciate you would prefer Visa and apologise for that. We do not perform any credit checks on our customers when they onboard to Monese. The only checks we do in some cases are to check a customers address/identity so we can confirm they are who they say they are to remain compliant with regulations and maintain our customer's safety. Anyone can sign up for a Monese account regardless of their nationality or if they live outside of the UK or if they have a good, bad or no credit history. Better yet, very shortly we will be allowing customers to sign up for our Euro accounts which will run simultaneously with our GBP account. You will receive a Euro IBAN and a new card Euro white card - you can sign up for the wait list at www.monese.com/euro. We hope that this clears things up in terms of not needing anything to do with a credit history, Rachel. We appreciate the feedback in regards to you not needing Direct Debits and preferring the Visa card and would love to hear from you if you have any more feedback at feedback@monese.com. All the best from all of us at Monese.

title: You pay, You Save
content: they charge you money for what you can get for free. as all you need to do is google cash plus and you will get something even better a card that you can do everything with as you would a bank account. that includes direct debits and standing orders!
reply: Hey!Our transparent fee of ¬£4.95 / month gives you access to what most would expect from a current account.One of the reasons we started Monese was to reveal the brutal hidden charges slapped onto customers by the traditional high street UK banks and let our customers save by paying a monthly fee with us instead of throwing away fortunes without even knowing about it. An average Monese customer saves money by paying our monthly fee over having a traditional bank account. We never try to up-sell products such as overdraft protection which can be as much as ¬£8.00 a month alone!Not only that, but to actually give the opportunity for the unbanked, that were turned out the door as they did not have a credit history or UK residential address, the equal right to have a bank account - And we wanted them to have it in minutes!Another huge point for us was that we wanted to create global on-demand banking. We knew customers would want to send money abroad to family or friends and the extortionate charges made by banks for foreign exchange could carry on no longer. That's why we let our customers send money abroad at rates up to 8x cheaper than the traditional UK high street banks so that their friends and family could get what they deserved instead of being fined for it.On top of these international transfers we wanted to let our customers have global usage of their Monese cards at a fraction of the price while letting them access the best possible foreign currency conversion, again saving up to 8x as the typical UK banks you would know well.These are but a few reasons that make us so much more transparent, cheaper and better than a traditional bank. The BEST part is that we are constantly adapting our product to fit our users wishes. We are always bringing in new features to make sure we are giving the best service we can possibly give.We hope that this clears the monthly fee up for you and you can see that even with a monthly fee and if you have any further questions please do send us your queries to feedback@monese.com.From all of us, our kindest regards!

content: i'm happy for this account
reply: Great news, Alban! Happy to have you on the Monese team :D

name: Florin Puitel
title: no happy at all
content: hi, my name is florin and i have an account with monese. everything was perfectly fine until a week ago when my account has been closed without any warning and elanation. my account is still blocked and i cannot access my money for over a week which is unacceptable
reply: Hi Florin,We are happy to hear that you have enjoyed the service up until recently.We have looked into the issue for you and have contacted you directly. We apologise for any inconvenience we have caused you, Florin, and look forward to speaking to you.We never want to disappoint our customers but we need to remain compliant with regulations and therefore in  exceptional circumstances we may have to block an account.All the best,Monese

name: Paul-Alexandru Atomi
title: Transfer money in few hours..
content: transfer money in few hours
reply: Hi Paul-Alexandru,We are sorry to hear that our faster payments aren't quite at the speed you require yet.However, we are constantly improving the product and I am sure you will be happy to hear that in the coming months we are going to be able to transfer funds every 30 minutes. We have noted that this is an issue for you, Paul-Alexandru, and will inform you the second that we improve the service. Until then, thank you very much for your feedback!

name: Naroll
title: Love the app
content: really good alternative from a normal bank account
reply: Hey Naroll,Thanks a lot for the 5 star review! We are really glad you haven't experienced any difficulties - At monese we are trying to create a simple and smooth alternative to a normal bank account and it makes us really happy to hear we are providing that for you :)

name: Colin
title: Gaming changing......
content: it took five minutes and no paper!! this is far removed from my last eerience of setting up a bank account, which took weeks and was a hugely frustrating process.i travel overseas regularly on business and holiday.) at the departure airport, and then use my credit card, or bank debit card, for larger eenditure (hotels, dinner etc. i have been throwing money away for years.i used the monese card over the weekend in a number of places and saved money. this is money that previously i was throwing away without thought

name: Andrew Agu
title: Avoid
content: allowed my account to be accessed by a fraudster they then closed my account without telling what's happened. and they did an illegal credit check on me

name: Jack
title: Monese is class!
content: it saved me a lot of money on fees abroad when in france and barbados. it didn't charge me anything for using an atm like my natwest card and i was able to make international transfers in the cool app at the spot rate too.as a person who travels a lot, i know it will be ideal for business and personal trips to other countries.spot on

name: James Fitz
title: Great
content: wanted an account that could track my spending rather than waiting three days for my transactions to show up on my statement with my natwest account

name: carly neave
title: Forever Sceptical - not anymore!
content: i'm one of those people who's always very wary about a great new deal with banks - i feel like there's going to be a hidden catch and end up having a load of interest bills i never knew about. i'm a travel writer and hence flying all the time so to save money every single transaction is just amazing - i feel like i'm making money!highly recommended!

name: Robin Young
title: Green Eyed Greed Got Me!
content: i was chuffed because i'd gained an era  which i figured would pay for a nice free boozy lunch on the slopes!it ended up being a very boozy and eensive long weekend and i ran out of cash! i was going to use my credit card but one of the lads said it'd cost me a packet with their foreign currency exchange fees. he had a monese card which i'd never heard of before and claimed he was getting spot rate with no fees! frankly i didn't really believe him so challenged him to prove it and he showed me the bill

name: kimberly
title: A real revelation to me!
content: i have a home abroad and the opportunity to send money over and withdraw money virtually at spot is incredible. it was always a pain trying to find the best rate, and monese has really solved a genuine headache for me! i have recommended it to loads of people as opening an account is always a difficult process, i have been a client of lloyds for over  years and have two business accounts, and it still took  weeks to open up a third business account!!!

name: Arthur Walsh
title: Dangerously good
content: one of the simplest set up processes had me instantly hooked on monese, but the best was yet to come once i found out how easy it was to use the app to make international transfers, and at spot rate as well! it's made spending money when travelling so much less of a hassle, thoroughly recommend to anyone thinking of joining, monese certainly are putting the ease back in money

name: Jack Opperman
title: Love it
content: exactly what my friend said it would be i got everything i would eect from a bank and only took me a few minutes to set up the account

name: Edward Stokes
title: Perfect for a traveller
content: i feel so secure knowing that anywhere i go i will never be hit by hidden charges from my bank and i can immediately track exactly the spot exchange rate i get abroad

name: Joe Dipre
title: fantastic
content: easy to set up, convenient to use and have saved a ton of money by using this!

name: Paul Sadler
title: Amazing
content: exactly what i needed - i send money back to my mum in france and i now use my monese account for every transfer! i get the best rates and i'm saving fortunes to what i was paying with my natwest account

name: Jamie Pitt
title: Super fast and great international transfers
content: set my account up because of a recommendation from a friend, i'm so happy he told me to. set it up in under  minutes and could start sending money abroad at nearly spot rate

name: Amy Olivia Crawford
title: Everything you'd expect from a bank
content: a friend recommended this to me and i couldn't believe how easy and quick it was to make an account

name: Matt Desmond Kealey
title: Fantastic service
content: eremely fast to set up and very happy with live tracking of my spending through notifications, which is a great feature

name: Charlie Smith
title: Fastest account I've ever made!
content: i made the account in literally a few minutes and i could send receiving money immediately!

name: Matt Swabey
title: Overalls a great way to bank especially for someone that travels!
content: it was also very quick and efficient to set up as don't have to provide credit history etc!

name: Jamie Ray
title: Changing the banking game
content: quick and easy to set up, and great for tracking my spending. also regularly transfer money abroad as part of my job and save a ton by avoiding eortionate fees!
reply: Hi Jamie,Many thanks - it's great to have you onboard!We are really happy you are using the international payments feature straight from your Monese balance, we wanted to make sure we could give our customers the best possible exchange rates and be transparent with our fees.We hope you carry on saving with us :)

name: Ieuan Owen
title: Saved me money!
content: i used my monese account abroad to avoid the hideous fees charged by the big banks.monese offer a transparent spot rate and flat fee, so you can avoid the big charges
reply: Hi Ieuan,Thank you for taking the time to leave a review. We make sure that everything we charge is transparent and to ensure our customers get the best possible exchange rates you can get when abroad.It makes us so happy knowing we can help save you money and will continue to do so!

name: Char Stott
title: Fantastic!
content: love it - it has saved me money and the customer service is great! thanks monese
reply: Amazing!We are so happy you love Monese, welcome aboard Char.

name: Cameron Scott
title: They freeze everyone's money...
content: i took a monese account as a secondary bank, and i liked the idea of the whole "app only" set up.i barely used the card, i left , on it which came from my rbs bank account, for  months. the first transaction i made was to pay a bt bill, instantly my account was frozen. i then received an email stating "due to aml we are closing your account, your funds will be returned to the bank within  days".how many peoples money do they hold for up to  days? i feel like this is a little troubling? do the maths. when people have proved who they are, have confirmed id and have no went out with the terms and conditions? i work in financial services myself, i understand kyc and aml regulations, i never breached any of these and monese have no appeal process to ask why they have closed your account or frozen it. i just do not recommend trusting this company with your money, escpially if you needing access to the money you hold on this account daily

name: Roo Aubeeluck
title: Simple Banking at its best.
content: opened my account on the train and received my card within a few days. i still cant get enough of how easy the transfers are, i have a santander mobile banking app and its the worst to use, have to register the person then send the money. also like to track to eenses, makes saving much easier

name: Chris
title: Easy, Simple Banking
content: opened account on mobile phone and received my card within  days. uploaded more documents and was full verifed member within  days or opening account.i was dubious at first and sent a small amount from my tsb account to see what happened, took a while to come through but this is becauase they use a rd party faster payment system at present so is only processed every few hours and not at weekends

name: Octopus
title: Easy & Convenient
content: easy to set up an account, upgrade and and use. loads of services included in the monthly fee! great value if you use the account a lot. can't wait for direct debits, which monese is saying will be available in the future

name: Nordica
title: Best UK bank account
content: no need to queue, simple onboarding process and you already have a bank account in your mobile app within some minutes!

name: Joe Allison
title: Very impressed with Monese
content: it was so fast and easy to open an account with monese. excellent customer service also, i would recommend to anyone in need of a bank account

name: Fayder Florez
title: Monese current account
content: no doubts, the best current account app in the market

name: Donna Care
title: SO EASY TO OPEN AN ACCOUNT!!!!
content: after years of being in and out of the uk without a real bank account, i found monese and now i can pay my rent from a local bank account

name: Henry
title: Account opened quickly
content: took me only few minutes to get monese bank account, have been struggling with barclays for ages

name: Ragnar M
title: Great new bank!
content: everything from the account opening to your statements is digital and really smooth

name: Lauri Haav
title: Opened a bank account during a taxi ride
content: i literally downloaded the app, made a picture of my id card, took a selfie, registered my address and got the bank account opened during a short taxi ride. sending money from my euro bank account to monese uk account required some era information which i failed to add so the customer support contacted me in order to finish the transaction

name: M. Daniel
title: An awesome alternative to traditional banks
content: monese is a fantastic solution for anyone that has recently arrived in the uk and needs a bank account to receive a uk salary. it's just like a regular bank, you can make payments using the app, receive pay / salary, send money abroad cheaply (pretty great at .% on top of the real rate) and just generally manage your money from anywhere. i use it as my main bank account daily and have had no issues!

name: Lemming
title: Monese is not what it says on the tin!
content: i have been using monese almost from the outset (more than  month by now), as i love to support start-ups and disruptive businesses, but there comes a time when one must eect even start-ups to be working fully and to deliver a quality service  unfortunately this is not the case with monese.over time i have eerienced issues with limits relating to cash withdrawals, both in uk and in germany, i have found out that i cannot make bank transfers to d party countries, i cannot move funds from my paypal account to my monese account, their support takes up to  weeks to answer even messages marked urgent, their support is only available between : and : uk time and only monday to friday, you can maximum have  , in your account at any given time  and i can go on. per month for the account, an account which turns out to basically be a pre-paid visa card!truth be told, i do like the philosophy that they sell, being a uk bank account for everyone living in eu where they offer standard current account features, but i am afraid that i feel they not even live up to that!monese, i am sorry, but i will now start to look for alternatives to you  you have disappointed me dramatically by "selling" a product which i feel you have not delivered!

name: lee chadwick
title: great bank low fees
content: monese is a new banking app that you can send fast money transfers from your mobile app so easy you can see what you spend what monies go in your account with real time up to the minute spends and regular updates, you get a contactless visa which is so easy nowadays, all your banking is done on your app and customer service is very helpful, at the moment they don't have the direct debit facilities but it is something their gonna be getting onboard very soon but its just a small fee of . a month so no charges for money withdrawals, no charge for depositing money or fast tranfers its all in the . month, the good part i love is you can go to a ''paypoint'' and deposit money instead of waiting in banks

name: Andrei
title: ok, but not enough!
content: there are some problems when i make my purchases in different stores, or when i withdraw money from atms
reply: Hello Andrei!Thanks for your positive review :)About the mentioned issues, we recommend that you contact our Support Team so they can explain exactly what happened to these transactions. Unfortunately, we cannot comment on any account specifics on a public platform.Thanks for your understanding!All the best,The Monese team

name: Vlad
title: AVOID!
content: i've made a transaction of   , uk to uk account , it was pending till october . i called them about ten times asking to cancel this transaction because i already paid to person with different account . instead of resolve the issue they just suspended my account , (with money in it of course) .all those prepaid accounts companies have one excuse "we are fca regulated company " , i wonder how did they get the license .i strongly advice you do not keep any money with any fca regulated prepaid accounts companies . unless you are ready to lose your money

name: Robert
title: I cannot topup from my Maestro Card‚Ä¶
content: with both of them i can topup my revolut account/card

name: Matteo Ricci
title: Conto bloccato / Blocked account
content: ****they blocked my account after a year that i use very little. they ask me for documentation on where the money came from

name: Birce
title: Horrible customer service
content: i guess asking for a debit card is the primary thing you could ever ask from your bank and should not take you weeks until you get it

name: Deimantas
title: Good app easy to use
content: sign up and order free card then make first payment with your card and you will get  into your account
reply: Hello Adrian!We're very sorry for any inconvenience caused to you because of this.Please remember that the referral bonus is allocated to the account once the first card transaction is concluded and successfully cleared, which sometimes might not happen instantly. You can always find more information about the referral program functioning on our website, app or FAQ :)All the best,The Monese team
